{"word":"ἐγχωρέω","slug":"ἐγχωρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐγχωρέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><i>to give room</i> for doing a thing, <i>to allow, permit</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:— <el>ἐγχωρεῖ</el>, <a href='S:impersonal'>impers.</a> <i>it is possible</i> or <i>allowable</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ἔτι ἐγχωρεῖ</el> <i>there</i> is yet <i>time</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/>"}]}